# 📚 Documentation Maintenance

## 🚨 After EVERY change, update the docs

Before finishing any task that changes behavior, entities, config, or API usage,
update the matching documentation. Code and docs must never drift apart.

### What to update (by change type)

| Change | Update |
| ------ | ------ |
| New/changed entity, sensor, switch, select, number | `docs/ENTITIES.md` + translations (`strings.json`, `en.json`, `pl.json`) |
| Alarms / events behavior | `docs/ALARMS_AND_EVENTS.md` |
| Schedules / calendar behavior | `docs/SCHEDULES.md` |
| Config flow / options / polling / device grouping | `docs/CONFIGURATION.md` |
| API endpoint usage | `docs/API_V1_DOCUMENTATION.md` |
| Dynamic entity logic | `docs/DYNAMIC_ENTITY_VALIDATION.md` |
| Breaking change / new major feature | `docs/MIGRATION.md` |
| Any user-facing change | `CHANGELOG.md` (newest entry on top) |

### README is a hub, not a manual

- Keep `README.md` short: summaries + links to `docs/`. Put full details in `docs/`.
- When adding a new doc under `docs/`, add it to the **Documentation** table in `README.md`.
- Verify every internal link points to a file that exists.

### Docs must match the real code

- Never document removed features. Example: schedules became **Calendar** entities
  (`calendar.py`) — text schedule sensors no longer exist, so docs must use the
  Calendar card, not `state_attr('sensor.*_schedule_*', 'monday')`.
- Expose **structured data**; let the dashboard render it (Jinja/Markdown card).
  Do not generate presentation strings (Markdown tables) inside the integration.

### Markdown anchors (TOC links)

- GitHub does NOT strip emoji variation selectors (U+FE0F), so headings like
  `## ⚙️ Configuration` break `#configuration` links. Prefer single-codepoint
  emoji (e.g. `🧰`) and link to the generated form (`#-configuration`), or omit
  emoji from headings used in the TOC.

### Before finishing

- [ ] Relevant `docs/*.md` updated
- [ ] `CHANGELOG.md` entry added for user-facing changes
- [ ] `README.md` links/table updated if docs were added
- [ ] Internal links resolve
- [ ] Markdown passes **pymarkdown** (config in `pyproject.toml` `[tool.pymarkdown]`:
      `MD013` line length 120, `MD033`/`MD024` disabled). Run `python -m pymarkdown scan <file>`.
